1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,444
Imagine this.

2
00:00:01,394 --> 00:00:03,548
You've built an amazing app.

3
00:00:03,548 --> 00:00:05,067
Users love it.

4
00:00:05,067 --> 00:00:09,817
Then one morning you wake up and your app is on the front page of Hacker News.

5
00:00:09,817 --> 00:00:14,096
Suddenly ten million people are trying to use your app at the same time.

6
00:00:14,096 --> 00:00:15,836
Your server crashes.

7
00:00:15,836 --> 00:00:18,144
Your users see error pages.

8
00:00:18,144 --> 00:00:19,923
Your boss is calling.

9
00:00:19,923 --> 00:00:23,346
This is the exact problem that Apache Kafka solves.

10
00:00:23,346 --> 00:00:26,942
And if you don't understand it, you WILL face this nightmare.

